- next: # unreleased
- v0.0.3:
  - Fix:
    - Consistent treatment of unicode strings in Perl and Praat
      backends
  - Changes:
    - Increased depended version of varargs to 0.0.6, to solve
      an issue with empty string variables
- v0.0.2:
  - New:
    - Implemented support for %B
  - Fix:
    - Ensure output of printf is printed to the info window
      unless otherwise specified by the user (by setting
      printf.stdout to true)
    - Make perl scripts replace newlines and tabs globally
    - Corrected some rounding errors with %g
    - Padding with the # flag applies to all octal numbers
    - Correctly parse (ie. discard) negative precision values
    - Ensure perl scripts receive parameter indices
    - Ensure strings are also zero-padded when using the 0 flag
- v0.0.1:
  - Initial release
